quran[11]{c,v,t,f}:
  92,19,"And not [giving] for anyone who has [done him] a favor to be rewarded{1}",footnotes:1:[i.e., without intending reciprocation for some benefit to himself.]
  92,20,"But only seeking the face [i.e., acceptance] of his Lord, Most High."
  92,21,"And he is going to be satisfied."
  96,7,"Because he sees himself self-sufficient."
  96,8,"Indeed, to your Lord is the return."
  96,9,"Have you seen the one who forbids"
  97,4,"The angels and the Spirit [i.e., Gabriel] descend therein by permission of their Lord for every matter.{1}",footnotes:1:[Bringing the exact measures apportioned for everything by Allāh in the course of the coming year.]
  97,5,"Peace it is{1} until the emergence of dawn.",footnotes:1:[Upon the believers.]
  98,1,"Those who disbelieved among the People of the Scripture and the polytheists were not to be parted [from misbelief]{1} until there came to them clear evidence",footnotes:1:[i.e., from their erroneous beliefs and superstitions.]
  98,2,"A Messenger from Allāh, reciting purified{1} scriptures",footnotes:1:[i.e., containing no falsehood.]
  98,3,"Within which are correct writings [i.e., rulings and laws]."